[Cron job]
A cron job is a scheduled task that allows you to run scripts or commands at specified intervals.
Cron jobs automate repetitive tasks, ensuring they run at scheduled times without manual intervention.
Ex. Backing up files, running system maintainance or sending email reports.
Cron uses a daemon (background process) called crond to execute scheduled tasks.
The configuration for these tasks is stored in a file called crontab.